Pandemonium erupted at the City King Hotel, Gusau, Zamfara State capital venue for the APC stakeholders meeting as Senator Kabir Marafa and former minister of State Communication, Alhaji Ikra Aliyu Bilbis engaged in a free for all fight. The two arch rivals engaged in exchange of blows. The fight generated tension as the supporters of the two factions were ready for acrimony.
LEADERSHIP reports that state director, DSS ordered his men to whisk Senator Marafa away, but his details attempted to resist, but however, Marafa asked his aides to calm and followed the DSS official to their office.Â  LEADERSHIP reports that, the two factions were set for show down as none of the faction was ready for compromise over the conduct of the primaries.